The United States congratulates Hassan Sheikh Mohamoud on becoming Somalia's new president and commends the Somali people for completing a significant political transition. The vote represents a milestone in building a representative government. The US urges Somalia's leaders to establish a new era of governance that is responsive, representative, and accountable. They encourage inclusivity, collaboration, and the strengthening of democratic institutions, stability, security, and improvements in the lives of citizens. The US will continue to support Somalia during this historic moment and calls on the international community to reaffirm its commitment to Somalia's future.